Class TieBreaker<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mrapp.apriori.TieBreaker<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the items, the tie-breaking strategy applies to
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TieBreaker.AssociationRuleTieBreaker, TieBreaker.ItemSetTieBreaker

    public abstract class TieBreaker<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<T>
    A tie-breaking strategy, which allows to decide, which one of two item sets or association rules should be sorted before the other one, if their heuristic values are equal.
    Since:
    1.1.0
